ital on creative industries","shortDescription":"Let us look at how key creative sectors such as music, or film are adjusting to the digital revolution. What is the new landscape for today’s artists?","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1b/7e/regular_1b7ea119-e307-4cf4-ab8b-507e3f3e373e.jpg"}}},{"title":"The rise of transmedia","shortDescription":"Transmedia refers to the mobilization of diverse media, platforms, and channels to spread a message or develop a cultural project. It is used to diversify audiences and mobilize them in a participatory way. ","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0f/ea/regular_0fea79ad-be87-4bfb-a876-fe80a03e908f.jpg"}}},{"title":"Week 1 wrap up","shortDescription":"Let us recap what we have learned this week","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ac/af/regular_acaf1de3-a812-440b-85f9-3be38196b64f.jpg"}}}]},{"title":"Cultural institutions in the digital age","activities":[{"title":"A new era for cultural policy?","shortDescription":"What does the digital era mean for cultural institutions? We will discuss changing cultural policies in an age of transnational cultural flows. ","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/4b/0f/regular_4b0f5636-78e7-4e1a-b21e-d7987d021c3e.jpg"}}},{"title":"Crowdfunding culture","shortDescription":"Crowdfunding has today become increasingly popular for cultural organisations. We will discuss the role it can play in financing culture.","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/7a/40/regular_7a403899-bc01-4b36-a211-b16c630639e6.jpg"}}},{"title":"Digitalised art worlds","shortDescription":"How has digital technology affected the art world? We will look at how different actors adapt to the digital era.","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/53/5f/regular_535f3073-d731-478d-9427-d3b3789f70a7.jpg"}}},{"title":"Week 2 wrap up","shortDescription":"Let's recap what we have learned this week!","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ce/0a/regular_ce0a31d8-ba65-4f90-b73c-2fb83ff2cb91.jpg"}}}]},{"title":"New threats and regulatory challenges in the age of the internet","activities":[{"title":"The emergence of new vulnerabilities","shortDescription":"From cyber-attacks to foreign influences on electoral processes: mapping the new threats in the digital era.","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/6e/45/regular_6e459786-20a6-41b5-b044-2d736ef6bbf6.jpg"}}},{"title":"Digital platforms as threats for the creative economy","shortDescription":"Digital platforms disrupt creative industries and generate issues with regards to privacy. How can they be better regulated? ","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/39/35/regular_3935f27a-1af9-4518-9e5d-20452488574d.jpg"}}},{"title":"Media pluralism in the digital era","shortDescription":"An unprecedented amount of news is spread nowadays. But there are increasing doubts about the quality and diversity of information. What are the new threats to media pluralism in the digital era?","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1d/f4/regular_1df4d39b-d088-4da3-9206-36524a858675.jpg"}}},{"title":"Discussing the impacts of new technologies on international cultural exchanges","shortDescription":"Which opportunities, challenges and threats do new technologies raise for the development of international cultural relations?","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/53/21/regular_53218391-9c34-4589-b2bd-c23b55c8d09e.jpg"}}},{"title":"Course wrap up","shortDescription":"Let's recap what we learned over these three Weeks!","imageAlt":"","image":{"regular":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/47/17/regular_4717b65e-6d28-4f8f-92c4-62d97984d437.jpg"}}}]}],"educators":[{"fullName":"Anna Triandafyllidou","initials":"AT","toParam":"6014441","profilePubliclyAccessible":true,"image":{"profileImage":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d4/96/profile_image_d496e8e4-c2a5-4608-8447-79057f81f326.JPG"}},"shortDescription":{"__html":"<p&gt;Anna Triandafyllidou is Canada Excellence Research Chair in Migration and Integration at Ryerson University, Toronto, Canada.</p&gt;"},"avatarColour":"purple"},{"fullName":"Jeremie Molho","initials":"JM","toParam":"4561430","profilePubliclyAccessible":true,"image":{"profileImage":{"url":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/4c/21/profile_image_4c21da55-0063-4929-8a91-3d0eff5264dc.jpg"}},"shortDescription":{"__html":"<p&gt;Jeremie Molho is Research Fellow at the European University Institute</p&gt;"},"avatarColour":"gold"}],"organisation":{"vectorLogoUrl":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8c/ca/8cca47b9-7f38-4952-a7a3-631dce748726.svg","logoAlt":"European University Institute logo","title":"European University Institute (EUI)","whiteVectorLogoUrl":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/19/9c/199c7881-ba3b-43b3-acb9-f8c34e8d5287.svg","vectorLogoAlt":"European University Institute logo","logoUrl":"https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d0/ed/d0edffae-56b3-49f2-b25a-c512e5308393.png","shortDescription":{"__html":"<p&gt;We are the European University Institute (EUI), the leading institute in Europe dedicated to social sciences and humanities. Founded in 1972 by the six original members of the then European Communities, the EUI has earned a reputation as a transnational hub of research and higher learning.</p&gt;\n"},"twitter":"EUI_EU","path":"/partners/eui","universityProfile":null},"coCreatingOrganisations":[],"learningOutcomes":[{"outcomeText":"Identify economic and organisational models emerging in the cultural economy as a result  of digital disruptions "},{"outcomeText":"Explore the key regulatory challenges at national and international levels"},{"outcomeText":"Design innovative frameworks for intercultural relations, using the power of new technologies"},{"outcomeText":"Develop a digital strategy to reach a wider audience and build global networks  "}],"details":{"promotedCoBrandingOrganisationText":"","outline":{"__html":"<p&gt;In the last two decades, the cultural sector has undergone a radical transformation due to the rise of new media technologies. The digital revolution has radically transformed the daily practice of international cultural relations.</p&gt;\n\n<p&gt;On this course you will explore how digital technology creates new opportunities in international cultural relations. You will learn about new trends in the cultural economy, regulatory challenges and emerging threats. You will also be introduced to tools to build a digital strategy in order to reach an international audience and establish global networks.</p&gt;\n"},"outlineTitle":"Explore the affects of digital technology on the cultural sector","courseSyllabus":{"__html":"<p&gt;<strong&gt;Digitalisation and the cultural economy</strong&gt;</p&gt;\n\n<ul&gt;\n  <li&gt;Impacts of the digital on creative industries</li&gt;\n  <li&gt;The rise of transmedia</li&gt;\n</ul&gt;\n\n<p&gt;<strong&gt;Cultural institutions in the digital age</strong&gt;</p&gt;\n\n<ul&gt;\n  <li&gt;A new era for cultural policy?</li&gt;\n  <li&gt;Crowdfunding culture</li&gt;\n  <li&gt;Digitalised art worlds</li&gt;\n</ul&gt;\n\n<p&gt;<strong&gt;New threats and regulatory challenges in the age of the internet</strong&gt;</p&gt;\n\n<ul&gt;\n  <li&gt;The emergence of new vulnerabilities</li&gt;\n  <li&gt;Digital platforms as threats for the creative economy</li&gt;\n  <li&gt;Media pluralism in the digital era</li&gt;\n</ul&gt;\n"},"syllabusEnabled":false,"hasOutlineOverLengthLimit":false,"requirements":{"__html":"<p&gt;This course is for anyone working in fields related to culture or technology